      public void initialize(URL url, ResourceBundle resourceBundle)
      Initializes the Modify Appointment screen with the data from the appointment the user selected to modify

      This method utilizes three lambda expressions which promote better code readability and reduce the amount of code required. With each lambda expression utilizing only one line of code, their functionality can be easily understood.

      Specified by:
      initialize in interface javafx.fxml.Initializable
      Parameters:
      url - The FXML location used to resolve relative paths for the root object, or null if the location is not known.
      resourceBundle - The resources used to localize the root object, or null if the root object was not localized.

    • onSaveAppt

      public void onSaveAppt(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws SQLException
      The onSaveAppt method which manages the modification of an existing appointment.

      The user edits information about an existing appointment, which is then compiled and added to the appointments table of the client_schedule database.

      This method calls the form validation class which validates the data and alerts there are problems with the input data.

      Parameters:
      event - Save Appointment button clicked
      Throws:
      SQLException - Signals an SQLException has occurred

    • sendAppt

      Sends the information about the Appointment selected to populate the ModifyAppointment text fields

      Parameters:
      appointment - Appointment to be modified
